{
  "_doc": "Duskmourn: House of Horror (DSK) Play + Collector recipes from Wizards' official 'Collecting Duskmourn' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-duskmourn). Duskmourn shipped Play + Collector boosters only — NO Draft Booster — so authoritative is true and draft is intentionally undefined. Sub-set codes: DSK = main set, SPG = Special Guests, DSC = Duskmourn Commander. Exact rates published for the Play rare/mythic slot, land slot, Special Guests replacement (1 in 64), and all Collector slots are used verbatim. Approximations: 'lurking evil' and 'paranormal frame' and 'mirror monster' and 'double exposure' and 'Japan Showcase' treatments have no dedicated filter — modeled with the nearest of showcase / borderless / extended_art (frame distinctions dropped); full-art manor lands via basic_land; the 1-in-4 lurking-evil/paranormal variants of specific commons/uncommons are folded into the common/uncommon slots as showcase-filtered outcomes. Specific finishes re-pointed to dedicated filters: in the Premium Foil Special Slot the 'Textured Foil Double Exposure' outcome now uses textured_foil, and both 'Fracture Foil Japan Showcase' outcomes now use fracture_foil, instead of the showcase stand-in. AUDIT 2026-06 (article re-verification): commons slot — SPG was 1.5625 per common sub-pull (×6 ≈ 9% of packs); article says 1 in 64 PLAY BOOSTERS → 0.26 per slot. Lurking Evil common rate corrected from 6%/slot to ~0.7%/slot (article: 2 of 81 commons substitute to LE 1-in-4 times pulled); uncommon LE from 10% to ~1%/slot (4 of ~100 uncommons, same conditional). NOTE: Lurking Evil prints are standard-frame variant printings (same card, new collector number) that Scryfall files as variations — excluded by include_variations=false at fetch, so these outcomes currently fall back to the regular print of the same rarity (economically identical, art-variant only). Collector slots verified verbatim against the article — no changes.",
